{"type":"message","id":"092c9ce4","parentId":"6e3e30ec","timestamp":"2026-06-24T10:03:25.966Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants to know how to test the backlink system. Let me think about what they can test:\n\n1. Test the daemon is working - it already runs automatically\n2. Add a new project and see the full flow\n3. Find new sites for a project\n4. Manually trigger a scan\n5. Check cards being sent\n\nSince the system is already running and scanning coinography.com, the easiest way to test would be:\n1. Add a new test project\n2. Or request a scan-now on an existing project\n3. Or add new source sites to scan\n\nLet me give them practical options to test the system.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nYou have a few options to test the system:\n\n### Option 1: Trigger a scan on existing project\n```bash\nmanage_projects.py scan-now --project-url https://coinography.com\n```\nThe daemon will pick it up within ~1 minute.\n\n---\n\n### Option 2: Add a test project\n```bash\nmanage_projects.py add --project-url https://yoursite.com --niche \"your niche\"\n```\nThe daemon will start harvesting sites for it automatically.\n\n---\n\n### Option 3: Find new source sites\n```bash\nmanage_projects.py find-sites --niche \"crypto\"\n```\nThen merge them with:\n```bash\nmerge_new_sites.py\n```\n\n---\n\n### Option 4: Check pending leads\n```bash\nmanage_projects.py status --project-url https://coinography.com\n```\n\n---\n\n### Option 5: Watch the daemon live\n```bash\ntail -f ~/.openclaw-backlink/logs/nexus_daemon.log\n```\n\n---\n\n**Quickest test:** Tell me a niche (e.g., \"DeFi\", \"AI tools\", \"gaming\") and I can add a test project right now — you'll see cards appear in the group when the daemon finds and approves leads."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"local-bifrost","model":"minimax.minimax-m2.5","usage":{"input":18101,"output":386,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":18487